    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-10-14T10:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-10-14T10:29:00-05:00" n="653"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d653">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.51/225</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Petrograd</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-10-14T19:00:00+03:31">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 14, 1917, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received October 19, 5.15 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1864.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>Impressed Roumanian Minister, often also <persName corresp="#p_VCJ1"
                        >Vopicka</persName>, with the necessity of having Washington authorized
                    agent to sign obligations. <persName corresp="#p_AC1">Angelescu</persName>,
                    Roumanian Minister to United States, whom I urged to go direct to Washington
                    instead of stopping in London two weeks, as planned, as did <persName
                        corresp="#p_VCJ1">Vopicka</persName> when both were here September 8. Allied
                        <pb facs="0806" n="732" xml:id="pg_732"/> Ambassadors had three meetings on
                    Roumanian needs, another Tuesday. Shall cable conclusion when reached.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
